New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo posted his fourth triple-double of the season
Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 11 points, grabbed 12 rebounds, and kept Milwaukee's offense clicking with his season-high 13 assists
Pre-Game Insights: Bucks coach Doc Rivers said Antetokounmpo's passing'set the whole tone to our team.'
Post-Match Reflections: Bucks coach Doc Rivers said it required stitches to stop the bleeding from Antetokounmpo's cut on his right little finger
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks had lost four of their last five matches, with all of those defeats coming against teams with losing records
Others: The Bucks snapped a two-game skid and handled the 8-28 Raptors convincingly
